0.2.2
    * fix apq8096 build
0.2.1
    * update to use new tof2_data_t type
    * reduce voxel size again to 0.15
    * improve warnings when VIO comes and goes
0.2.0
    * update defaults for robot radius, voxel size
    * allow flying into unknown areas by default
0.1.9
    * remove voxl-vision-px4 dependency
    * pose pipe rename
0.1.7
    * voxl-vision-px4 to voxl-vision-hub transition
0.1.6
    * added esdf to mesh_api, serves it up in a human readable format
    * added more esdf pub options
0.1.5
    * multi tof support
    * bug fix for multi pointcloud input rates
    * now sending aligned pointclouds with proper timestamps, using new id field in ptcloud meta
    * added service file
0.1.4
    * added some better handling for failed mesh creation/writes
0.1.3
    * changed default mesh path to no longer include an extension
    * added support for mesh forwarding (from buffer) and mesh saving to disk
    * formats for above are: .ply, .obj, .gltf
    * fixed cmake warnings
0.1.2
    * added mesh_endpoint for portal, basic api to receive mesh in ply format
0.1.1
    * Swapped to use voxl-eigen3
0.1.0
    * Major changes to mapping
    * Major changes to planning architecture
0.0.7
    * update to match latest voxl-voxblox
0.0.6
    * New CI Stuff
0.0.6
    * costmap slider level control cmds added, calculating relative height based on map bounds
    * costmap sending voxel_size in z coords
    * costmap doubles->floats
    * updated depth_pipe cb flow
    * NEEDS voxl-portal >= v0.2.4 for these features
0.0.5
    * patch for vvpx4 trajectory_interface updates
0.0.4
    * support up to 5 depth inputs, 4 of which are generic pointcloud topics
    * individual data rates per pipe
    * mesh/visual generation + esdf updates in own thread
0.0.3
    * stereo / tof option, new template
0.0.2
    * loco tuning, skeleton removal, rrt* improvements, pointcloud downsampling algo added
0.0.1
    * initial release, mapping and path planning
